Yes — that explains the remaining behavior.

In disconnected/OpenShift mirrored environments, the ovnkube-upgrades-prepuller daemonset commonly gets stuck because nodes cannot pull the new OVN images from the mirrored registry properly.

Your cluster is actually healthy now:

no degraded MCP

no degraded network operator

all nodes Ready

control plane stable


The upgrade is waiting only for OVN rollout completion.

Most likely root cause in your disconnected setup:

one or more OVN images for 4.19.24 are missing in your mirror registry

OR ImageContentSourcePolicy/ImageDigestMirrorSet mismatch

OR node pull secret issue

OR stale prepuller pod


Check this immediately:

oc get pods -n openshift-ovn-kubernetes

Look for:

ImagePullBackOff

ErrImagePull

ContainerCreating

Pending


Then inspect failing pod:

oc describe pod -n openshift-ovn-kubernetes <podname>

Especially check Events section.

Also verify daemonsets:

oc get ds -n openshift-ovn-kubernetes

Very likely you will see something like:

DESIRED  CURRENT  READY  UP-TO-DATE
3        3        2      3

That single unavailable pod is blocking completion.

In disconnected clusters, common fix is:

1. Verify mirrored image exists in local harbor/quay


2. Verify pullspec resolution


3. Delete stuck prepuller pod



Example:

oc delete pod -n openshift-ovn-kubernetes <stuck-pod>

The daemonset recreates it.

Also verify node can pull image:

oc describe pod -n openshift-ovn-kubernetes <stuck-pod> | grep -A20 -i image

You may see:

unauthorized

manifest unknown

no route to host

x509

timeout


Another important point:

Your RetrievedUpdates=False due to DNS failure to api.openshift.com is completely normal in disconnected environments and NOT blocking the upgrade.

The real blocker is only:

OVN rollout completion


Also:

machine-config still showing 4.18.17 while MCP updated is normal during late-stage reconciliation

it usually flips after network operator completes


So at this stage:

do NOT reboot nodes

do NOT force another upgrade

do NOT manually modify CVO


Focus only on the stuck OVN daemonset/pod/image pull.
